riddle_judgement.prompt_template:
You are judging a riddle contest. A monster asked this riddle:

Riddle: {riddle}

The intended answer is: {correct_answer}

The player answered: {player_answer}

Judge SEMANTICALLY and LENIENTLY: the player is correct if their answer means the same thing as the intended answer, even with different wording, capitalization, spelling mistakes, articles (a/an/the), or a synonym. The player is wrong only if their answer refers to something genuinely different.

Respond with valid JSON in this exact format:
{{"correct": true, "verdict": "One short in-character sentence from the monster reacting to the answer - gracious in defeat if correct, gleeful if wrong."}}

